### Problem Description

When using a compound retriever, any `inner_hits` defined in its sub-retrievers are not propagated to the top-level retriever and are not part of the final results. 

### Steps to Reproduce

E.g. using `inner_hits` on a `semantic` query: 
```
POST retrievers_example/_search
{
    "retriever": {
        "rrf": {
            "retrievers": [
                {
                    "standard": {
                        "query": {
                            "nested": {
                                "path": "inference_field.inference.chunks",
                                "query": {
                                    "sparse_vector": {
                                        "field": "inference_field.inference.chunks.embeddings",
                                        "inference_id": "my-elser-endpoint",
                                        "query": "some query text"
                                    }
                                },
                                "inner_hits": {
                                    "size": 2,
                                    "name": "inference_chunks",
                                    "_source": [
                                        "inference_field.inference.chunks.text"
                                    ]
                                }
                            }
                        }
                    }
                },
                {
                    "standard": {
                        "query": {
                            "match_all": { } 
                        }
                    }
                }
            ],
            "rank_window_size": 10,
            "rank_constant": 1
        }
    }
}
```

